,,, 4-port USB Hub Controller;Genesys Logic;GL850G;;1; |stock_os=Linux;2.6.33.5;OpenWrt-deriv; |802dot11_protocols=abgn |default_ssid=ZyXEL |default_ssid_regex=^ZyXEL$ |default_ip=192.168.1.1 |default_pass=1234 |oui=C8:6C:87 |oui_eth=C8:6C:87 }} {{TagLine|Simultaneous Dual-Band Wireless N Media Router}} :[http://www.zyxel.com/products_services/nbg5715.shtml Product Page] :[ftp://ftp2.zyxel.com/NBG5715/datasheet/NBG5715_3.pdf Datasheet] {{â€¢}} [ftp://ftp2.zyxel.com/NBG5715/quick_start_guide/NBG5715_001.pdf Manual] :[ftp://ftp2.zyxel.com/NBG5715/ Downloads] : [ftp://ftp2.zyxel.com/NBG5715/firmware/NBG5715_1.00(AAAG.5)C0.zip FW v.1.00(AAAG.5)C0] The [[Mindspeed]] ''Comcerto'' 1000 (M83241G-13) CPU is the main SoC for device. :The RT3883 is apparently controlled via an MII interface (it's in ''iNIC'' mode). :The RT3593 appears to be controlled via the Comcerto's PCI bus. The firmware provided by ZyXEL is ~14.5MB. :The stock firmware is an '''OpenWrt'''-dervative firmware. :The stock WebUI is a modified LuCI. "45-402-000341" is silkscreened on the board shown below. :The default SSID for both bands is '''ZyXEL'''. The power adapter included with the device is a :'''DVE''' DSA-24CA-12 120200 (12V, 2A). ===Additional external links=== *[https://openwrt.org/toh/zyxel/nbg5715 On the '''OpenWrt''' Wiki] *[https://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?id=33652 On the '''OpenWrt''' forums] *http://nbg5715.shy.cz/GPL/ :NBG5715_100AAAG2_open_code.tar.bz2 (04-May-2012 19:44 759M) ===Serial=== Telnet would seem to be enabled by default. :Credentials of '''root''':1234 for a router w/ default settings worked fine.. ===cpuinfo=== {{SCollapse|cat /proc/cpuinfo |
